"#feedbackModal_main_2532489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104trf1665702913602.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/trf1665702913602.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/trf1665702913602.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"trf1665702913602\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Money Packing Codes\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">For Numeric fields that deal solely with amounts of money, you can specify a \n \nmoney packing code.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"trf1665702913602__p_d44648e1_d44649e1_d44650e1\">If the DBMS supports a money data type, the database connector maps these codes to the appropriate money data type. Otherwise, the connector maps them to the appropriate numeric or double-precision data type, depending on the desired precision. See the relevant connector documentation for your DBMS for information about how your connector will map the various M packing codes.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Money Packing Codes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\">\n Uniface Packing Code\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"2\">\n Explanation\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__3\">\n Uniface Data Types\n </th>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__4\">\n Numeric\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__1\">\n M1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__2\">\n Money: 8-byte integer\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__3 trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__4\">\n Y\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__1\">\n M2\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__2\">\n Money: double-precision floating point storage\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__3 trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__4\">\n Y\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__1\">\n M4\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__2\">\n Sybase internal money data type\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__3 trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__4\">\n Y\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__1\">\n M6\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__2\">\n Sybase small money format\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__3 trf1665702913602__table_d4310e1_d4311e1_d4312e1__entry__4\">\n Y\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"trf1665702913602__note_w4428ab1b5b5_w4429ab1b5_w4430ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The <code class=\"ph codeph\">M1</code> packing code is not the same as the\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">I8</code> packing code, even though they both use 8-byte integer storage. The\n         actual format of the data stored is incompatible.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"trf1665702913602__section_mdb_gt2_ncc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d674003e150\">Scaling</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"trf1665702913602__p_d44654e1_d44655e1_d44656e1\">Uniface always applies a scaling of two (that is, two\n            decimal places). You cannot specify a scaling when defining <code class=\"ph codeph\">M</code> packing\n            codes.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Range of values for M packing codes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1__entry__1\">Packing code </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1__entry__2\">Range of possible entries </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">M1</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1__entry__2\">+/- 922,337,203,685,477.58 </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">M2</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"trf1665702913602__table_d4313e1_d4314e1_d4315e1__entry__2\">Exponent:(10 +/-38 ) <p class=\"p\">Accuracy of mantissa (\n                           DBMS-dependent): 16 digits</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gpd1665702757526.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes for Numeric Data</a><p>The Uniface Numeric and Float data types are associated with many packing codes.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsp1665702531534.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Connectors</a><p>To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Money Packing Codes Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Money Packing Codes For Numeric fields that deal solely with amounts of money, you can specify a money packing code. If the DBMS supports a money data type, the database connector maps these codes to the appropriate money data type. Otherwise, the connector maps them to the appropriate numeric or double-precision data type, depending on the desired precision. See the relevant connector documentation for your DBMS for information about how your connector will map the various M packing codes. Table 1. Money Packing Codes Uniface Packing Code Explanation Uniface Data Types Numeric M1 Money: 8-byte integer Y M2 Money: double-precision floating point storage Y M4 Sybase internal money data type Y M6 Sybase small money format Y CAUTION: The M1 packing code is not the same as the I8 packing code, even though they both use 8-byte integer storage. The actual format of the data stored is incompatible. Scaling Uniface always applies a scaling of two (that is, two decimal places). You cannot specify a scaling when defining M packing codes. Table 2. Range of values for M packing codes Packing code Range of possible entries M1 +/- 922,337,203,685,477.58 M2 Exponent:(10 +/-38 ) Accuracy of mantissa ( DBMS-dependent): 16 digits Related Links Packing Codes for Numeric Data The Uniface Numeric and Float data types are associated with many packing codes. Database Connectors To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}